A young man died of a gunshot wound on Friday at a water treatment plant in Rosettenville Johannesburg.Paramedics received a call from the local authorities for medical assistance ER24 said in a statement. Cape Town s water greedy households face fines and water cuts It is understood that the man had been chased by the local authorities after an alleged hijacking ER24 said.Numerous enforcement officers and a police helicopter were on the scene when the paramedics arrived at the plant. They were instructed to be on stand-by but at a safe distance. Is your suburb affected by water cuts? Check this list ER24 said that after a short time the paramedics were called into a building where they found the body of the man believed to be in his 20s. Local authorities will be conducting an investigation into the matter. 